adpki (0.1.16) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added runtime validation before starting the AD-PKI setup wizard.
    - adpki-setup now checks whether adpki-install has been completed.
    - Setup is blocked if ADPKI_RUNTIME_INSTALLED is not set to true.
    - Added checks for required application payloads:
      /opt/adpki/backend/artisan
      /opt/adpki/frontend/dist/index.html
      /opt/adpki/ca-core/adpki-ca

  * Added setup step 3: database connection configuration.
    - Added interactive database setup for AD-PKI.
    - Supports existing PostgreSQL servers.
    - Supports locally installed PostgreSQL mode.
    - Writes database configuration to /etc/adpki/backend.env.
    - Stores setup database values in /etc/adpki/setup.env.
    - Performs PostgreSQL connection checks before continuing.

  * Added setup step 4: database schema installation.
    - Added controlled schema import using AD-PKI schema v1.
    - Added schema source path:
      /usr/share/adpki/database/adpki_schema_v1.sql
    - Added support for importing the prepared PostgreSQL schema.
    - Added Laravel seeder execution after schema installation.
    - Keeps seeders available for default roles, permissions and notification events.

  * Improved setup wizard structure.
    - Added dedicated setup common helper functions.
    - Added setup logging under /var/log/adpki/setup.
    - Added setup state handling under /var/lib/adpki/setup.
    - Added step tracking for completed setup steps.

  * Improved installer and setup separation.
    - Debian installer remains responsible for system/runtime preparation.
    - adpki-setup is responsible for functional AD-PKI configuration.
    - Root CA, Intermediate CA, WebUI TLS and Admin User setup remain in later setup steps.

 -- Ali Danakiran <danakiranali@gmail.com>  Sun, 10 May 2026 16:20:00 +0200

