adpki (0.1.14) stable; urgency=medium

  * Improved AD-PKI runtime installer stability.
  * Added PostgreSQL mode distinction between existing PostgreSQL server and
    new local PostgreSQL server installation.
  * Updated installer database selection wording.
  * Added readable database mode labels in installer output.
  * Added PostgreSQL 17.x version policy with minimum required version 17.9.
  * Changed PostgreSQL installation from exact package pinning to version
    policy validation for PostgreSQL 17.x >= 17.9.
  * Changed PHP installation to allow PHP 8.4.x security updates while
    requiring PHP >= 8.4.16.
  * Added runtime package hold handling for AD-PKI related Debian packages.
  * Added /etc/adpki/held-packages.list to document held runtime packages.
  * Improved installer logging for step-based runtime installation.
  * Replaced apt usage with apt-get in installer scripts for better scripting
    compatibility.
  * Improved Podman/container compatibility by skipping live service checks
    when systemd is not running.
  * Fixed installer output to use PostgreSQL version policy label instead of
    removed exact-version variable.
  * Improved install.env generation for Webserver, PostgreSQL, PHP, Node.js
    and Go runtime metadata.

